node.text:
Good people could still be horrible parents and to see people and kids that are torn between love and hate is the most heartbreaking thing in the world. My heart goes out to children with parents they can not fully love. Please know that you're not a horrible person for wanting out from a relationship that doesn't work for you, no matter how perfect the other person could be as an individual.
Photos and caption by @storysellercomics

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RegenHealth on September 02, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Nate Postlethwait @nate_postlethwait Please be patient with those who have a hard time articulating how they feel. Many of those people grew up in @nate_postlethwait environments where no matter what they said or how they said it, it it was not enough to be heard. Their default to feel safe was to stop sharing. Again, patience please.'.

node.text:
Communication is difficult, and when someone struggles with expressing themselves it leaves those closest to them defaulting to their own narratives or making assumptions. I would just like to make a few points about communication:⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1). Many people who do not know how to communicate or express themselves grew up in homes where they attempted on a regular basis to express themselves and were shut down. Over time, they felt it was safer to suffer silently rather than open up and try again. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
2). In that space, people tend to feel the weight of not being seen and heard. That compounds with their environment and over time they become void with words to share their experience.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
3). These are people who deserve safe space, safe people, and a guarantee that when they speak up they will be heard. Regardless of their age now, if they grew up in an environment like this, expressing themselves is terrifying. No kid has the mental capacity to understand being dismissed or misunderstood. They take information and do whatever they can to make sense of it, but rarely does that guide toward internal affirmation. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This is a friendly reminder that most people who don’t know how to express themselves or communicate what’s going on inside of them, may also not know why. Pushing or forcing them to do so may also be triggering their survival from long ago. Compassion, curiosity, and patience go a long way in connecting in the space.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Do you have a hard time communicating how you feel?

Photo & caption by @nate_postlethwait
